The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, March 20, 2005 

 Chief justice to take oath

 OUR LEGAL REPORTER

 Calcutta, March 19: Justice Vikas Sridhar Sirpurker will be sworn in as Chief Justice of Calcutta High Court tomorrow by governor Gopal Krishna Gandhi at the high court building.

 Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee and his cabinet colleagues are scheduled to attend the programme.

 Calcutta High Court will have a permanent chief justice after a gap of a year. Former Chief Justice Ashok Kumar Mathur was promoted as a Supreme Court judge in April 2004. Since then, three judges ? Justices A.. Roy, .A. Chowdhury and Ashok Kumar Ganguly ? have taken charge as acting chief justices of the high court.

 Born on August 22, 1946, at Chandrapur in Maharashtra, Sirpurker joined the Nagpur Court Bar Association in 1969. He was appointed a judge of Mumbai High Court in 1992 and was later promoted as chief justice of Uttaranchal High Court in July 2004.

 Sirpurker is a co-opted member of the education committee of the Bar Council of India. 




